						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dwedit wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">This of course assumes that sprite draw order or priority doesn't matter at all.</div><br />Precisely. When I want to preserve the sprite order within an object, I randomize the order in which entire objects are drawn, and the objects get to chose which end of the OAM they want to use, so there are 2 global layers that are preserved. Also, objects are free to draw sub-objects at the time they're drawn, so they can make sure that explosions and other effects always show up in front of them.</div>

